import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['Miles_per_Gallon'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Miles_per_Gallon')
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Miles per Gallon')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Miles_per_Gallon?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['Cylinders'], data['Horsepower'], c=data['Cylinders'], cmap='viridis', label='Cylinders')
    plt.xlabel('Cylinders')
    plt.ylabel('Horsepower')
    plt.title('How does the number of Cylinders affect the Horsepower?', wrap=True)
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Cylinders")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Year'].dt.year

    plt.plot(data['Year'], data['Miles_per_Gallon'])
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Miles per Gallon')
    plt.title('How has the Miles_per_Gallon changed over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Miles per Gallon'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
